    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Use tools in preference to unskilled help to lighten a programming task, even if you have to detour to build the tools and expect to throw some of them out after you\u2019ve finished using them.")), mdx("h4", null, "Uniform Interface"), mdx("p", null, "All programs must use the same I/O interface to be able to connect any program\u2019s output to any program\u2019s input. In Unix, that interface is a file (or, more precisely, a file descriptor). A file is just an ordered sequence of bytes."), mdx("p", null, "Unix programs read from ", mdx("inlineCode", {
