  }, "stdin/stdout"), " be an arbirtrary file."), mdx("p", null, "Running on a single machine is the biggest limitation of Unix tools."), mdx("h3", null, "MapReduce & Distributed Filesystems"), mdx("p", null, "Like Unix tools, MapReduce normally doesn't have side-effects -- It takes in input, and produces an output."), mdx("p", null, "MapReduce jobs read and write files on a distributed filesystem -- HDFS (Hadoop Distributed Filesystem) in Hadoop's implementation of MapReduce."), mdx("p", null, "HDFS is based on the shared-nothing principle."), mdx("p", null, "HDFS consists of a daemon process running on each machine, exposing a network service that allows other nodes to access files stored on that machine."), mdx("p", null, "A central server called the ", mdx("inlineCode", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "NameNode"), " keeps track of which file blocks are stored on which machine."), mdx("p", null, "Conceptually, it is one big filesystem that can use the space on the disks of all machines running the daemon."), mdx("p", null, mdx("img", _extends({
