    "src": "hdfs_architecture.gif",
    "alt": null
  }))), mdx("p", null, "Replication is used to tolerate machine and disk failures. Replication may mean simply several copies of the same data on multiple machines, or an erasure coding scheme such as Reed\u2013Solomon codes, which allows lost data to be recovered with lower storage overhead than full replication."), mdx("h4", null, "MapReduce Job Execution"), mdx("p", null, "MapReduce is a programming framework with which you can write code to process large datasets in a distributed filesystem like HDFS."), mdx("p", null, "The pattern of MapReduce is similar to the example above in Simple Log Analysis:"), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "li"
  }, "Read a set of input files, and break it up into records. In the web server log example, each record is one line in the log (that is, \\n is the record separator).")), mdx("li", {
